            <h1 class="post-title">Credentials</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="post-content">
            <h6 id="background">Background</h6>

<p>My educational background is in <a href="https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm14/webprogram/Paper28020.html">Geology</a> to which I credit my patience and ability to endure long stretches of work with the ungodly amount of hours spent staring down the hole of a microscope. Ultimately, I didn't see myself doing lab work for the foreseeable future (I still haven't lost my love for the outdoors though!) and decided to pursue something I absolutely enjoyed: web development.</p>

<h6 id="about">About</h6>

<p>When time allows it, I brew beer. I will probably never be Jim Koch, but the process and stylistic choices of a tradition that hearkens back to the days of yore. Also, I take poetry very, very seriously which I think pairs absurdly well with programming as much of language and DSL design (draw close parallels with it) is centered around the author's diction and the Principle of Good Enough. Parallels are close</p>

<h6 id="webdevelopment">Web Development</h6>

<p>I consider myself stack-agnostic, but I truly enjoy the back-end (Ruby, Rails, TDD, SQL, etc.) and consider it my strongest suit. Fundamentals are extremely important to me which is why I also consider myself tool-agnostic; my experience with Backbone is only important insofar as my quality of Javascript and JQuery.</p>

<h6 id="theteamimlookingfor">The Team I'm Looking For</h6>

<p>I'm looking for a place where I can contribute and grow with a goal-oriented team that takes pride in their work and product and pushes the idea of life-long learning. I also want that team to place great importance on being open to ideas in the workplace. </p>

<h6 id="recentprojects">Recent Projects</h6>

<p><strong>Open Source Watch</strong> <br />
- Tracks the top 100,000 repositories' activity on Github in real-time <br />
- 1.2 million requests per day <br />
- Highlights: parallel server coordination, SQL tuning, custom priority queue controlled by frequency distribution <br />
- <a href="http://">Article</a> / <a href="http://localhost:2368/credentials/opensourcewatch.io">Site</a> / <a href="https://github.com/opensourcewatch/curation-scraper">Source</a> </p>

